Most language learning products are
geared towards letting you to achieve a
survival level in the language

1. Dabbling

2. Survival

3. Functional

4. Fluent

5. Professionally Competent


Acquiring a Language vs Learning a Language

The first language is acquired through exposure,
processing is subconscious, and trying
to apply grammar rules in real time is
difficult and will never lead to a level
of proficiency similar to that of natives

 